               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1047" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1047" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1047" type="surname" value="BARTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1047" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BARTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a shop at Old Brentford. The prisoner came to my shop on Saturday evening the 18th of Feb.—she bought some tea,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184302270195"></xptr>
               <p>sugar, and butter, and I saw her take a piece of bacon off the butter counter and bring it to the grocery counter—my shopman served her, and while he went for something else she took this bacon—I saw her going out—I stopped her, and brought her back—I asked what she had in her apron—she said, "Nothing"—I opened her apron and found this bacon—it is mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Was it not in the middle of the shop? I told you to weigh it and I would pay you. <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, it was not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
